### User Management API v2.0.0 - Bug Fix Validation Test Suite
### Tests for all bug fixes and improvements
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@secureUrl = https://localhost:7000

---

### SECTION 1: BASIC ENDPOINTS
### ===================================

### 1.1 Health Check - Verify API is running and version is 2.0.0
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 1.2 Get all users (should include sample data)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users

---

### SECTION 2: BUG FIX #1 - EMAIL FORMAT VALIDATION
### ===================================

### 2.1 Create user with valid email format (SHOULD PASS)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Valid",
  "lastName": "Email",
  "email": "valid.user@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Software Engineer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2023-03-10",
  "isActive": true
}

### 2.2 Create user with INVALID email format (missing @) - SHOULD FAIL
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Invalid",
  "lastName": "Email",
  "email": "notanemail.com",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2023-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 2.3 Create user with INVALID email format (missing domain) - SHOULD FAIL
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Invalid",
  "lastName": "Email",
  "email": "user@",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2023-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 2.4 Create user with INVALID email format (missing local part) - SHOULD FAIL
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Invalid",
  "lastName": "Email",
  "email": "@domain.com",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2023-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

---

### SECTION 3: BUG FIX #2 - STRING WHITESPACE VALIDATION
### ===================================

### 3.1 Create user with whitespace-only firstName - SHOULD FAIL
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "     ",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "email": "whitespace.test@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Tester",
  "department": "QA",
  "hireDate": "2023-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 3.2 Create user with whitespace-only lastName - SHOULD FAIL
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "   ",
  "email": "whitespace2.test@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Tester",
  "department": "QA",
  "hireDate": "2023-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 3.3 Create user with trimmed whitespace (SHOULD PASS)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "  John  ",
  "lastName": "  Doe  ",
  "email": "trimmed.user@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "  Senior Engineer  ",
  "department": "  Engineering  ",
  "hireDate": "2023-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

---

### SECTION 4: BUG FIX #3 - HIREDATE VALIDATION
### ===================================

### 4.1 Create user with HireDate in the FUTURE - SHOULD FAIL
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Future",
  "lastName": "Employee",
  "email": "future.employee@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2099-12-31",
  "isActive": true
}

### 4.2 Create user with HireDate too far in PAST - SHOULD FAIL
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Ancient",
  "lastName": "Employee",
  "email": "ancient.employee@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "1800-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 4.3 Create user with valid HireDate (SHOULD PASS)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Valid",
  "lastName": "HireDate",
  "email": "valid.hiredate@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2022-06-15",
  "isActive": true
}

