### SECTION 7: BUG FIX #7 - ID VALIDATION
### ===================================

### 7.1 GET user with NEGATIVE ID - SHOULD FAIL
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/-1

### 7.2 GET user with ZERO ID - SHOULD FAIL
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/0

### 7.3 PUT user with NEGATIVE ID - SHOULD FAIL
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/-1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2023-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 7.4 DELETE user with NEGATIVE ID - SHOULD FAIL
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/users/-1

---

### SECTION 8: EXCEPTION HANDLING
### ===================================

### 8.1 GET with valid ID (should not crash)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1

### 8.2 POST with all validation errors - should handle gracefully
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "   ",
  "lastName": "   ",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "jobTitle": "",
  "department": "",
  "hireDate": "2099-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 8.3 PUT non-existent user - should return 404 gracefully
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/99999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Ghost",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "ghost@example.com",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2023-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

